title: The Looney Beginning
description: Bugs Bunny narrates how Buster and Babs Bunny were created by a cartoonist on a deadline to come up with a new concept for a great new cartoon; and they wound up having to create Acme Acres, all the characters, and get their scripts back from the villain, Montana Max, who stole them to create his own show.

title: A Quack in the Quarks
description: Plucky's incessant brags about heroism get him in trouble when two alien ducks posing as foreign exchange students kidnap him to return to their home planet to defeat their enemy, Duck Vadar; and it's up to Buster, Babs and Hamton to follow after the aliens and rescue Plucky.

title: The Wheel O' Comedy
description: Includes "Spectacular Day," "Devil Doggie," "Optical Illusion" and "Win, Lose Or Kerplowie." Buster and Babs are replaced by the Wheel of Comedy, Elmyra adopts Dizzy in the misperception he's a puppy, Furrball's confused when he picks up 3-D glasses and Buster interferes with a rigged game show.

title: Test Stress
description: Includes "Never Too Late To Loon," "Lil' Sneezer" and "To Bleep Or Not To Bleep." Plucky tries to cheat on a math exam, Sylvester gives Furrball an assignment to catch a mouse, and a swearing Rooster asks Buster to help him get a date with Shirley.

title: The Buster Bunny Bunch
description: A satire of "The Mickey Mouse Club" sees Buster suffering at the hands of a pumped-up Arnold at the gym in "Buffed Bunny," Dizzy receiving justice at the hands of fate after squashing bugs in "Squish," and Babs driving away all her friends with her dead-on imitations in "Born To Be Riled."

title: Her Wacky Highness
description: Fed up with both school and her family, Babs decides to run away to Wackyland, figuring she'll fit right in. However, she soon begins to have second thoughts.

title: Journey to the Center of Acme Acres
description: Buster and Babs set out to set out to rescue Hamton and Plucky from a crevice left by an earthquake and discover the source of the recent tremblings of the ground.

title: Stuff That Goes Bump in the Night
description: Buster's poltergeist comes back to haunt Montana Max after he drops a house on the rabbit in "Home Wrecker." Elmyra's pet-of-the-month club delivers a vampire bat in "Fang You Very Much." And Hamton faces off against a mosquito in "Easy Biter."

title: It's Buster Bunny Time
description: The gang spoofs Howdy Doody in "Buster Bunny Bunch," the Roadrunner/Wiley Coyote competition in "Bag That Bunny," Robin Leach in "Lifestyles Of The Rich And Rotten" and classic al music in "The Anvil Chorus."

title: Looking Out for the Little Guy
description: Elmyra adopts Sneezer when he's left on her doorstep in "Awful Orphan." Plucky tries to stop Montana in "The Re-Return Of The Toxic Revenge," and a dog tries to protect baby chickens from the prowling Furrball in "Bird-Dog Afternoon."

title: Starting from Scratch
description: A flea makes a courageous journey to find his family in a spoof of "An American Tail."

title: Hare-Raising Night
description: Buster goes on a mission to stop the mutant experiments of Dr. Gene Splicer.

title: Furrball Follies
description: Furrball pretends to be a dog when he meets a blind couple who hates cats in "K-9 Kitty." In "Aroma Amore," a paint stripe down Furrball's back attracts Fifi.

title: The Acme Acres Zone
description: A "Twilight Zone" spoof including "A Walk On The Flip Side," where rabbit-hating Montana wakes up as a bunny; "A Bacon Strip," in which Hamton is duped into skinny-dipping; and in "Senserely Yours, Babs," Babs loses her sense of humor.

title: Life in the 90's
description: Hamton takes Plucky and the Bunnys to a fancy restaurant in "Whining Out," Max tries to bilk Buster in "Paper Trained," and Babs fights smokers in "Butt Out."

title: Rock 'N' Roar
description: Buster finds a dinosaur egg and mistakes it for his soccer ball, until it hatches into a tyrannosaurus Rex. Buster names him Rover and makes a pet out of him, but Montana Max tries to hunt the dinosaur down for his own uses and it's up to Buster and his friends to return Rover to where he belongs.

title: Prom-ise Her Anything
description: Acme Looniversity is abuzz as the prom approaches. Buster fears his dark secret -his profound inability to dance- will be revealed. Babs is on pins and needles, waiting for Buster to ask her out. Elmyra nurses her unrequited crush on Montana Max, who flees to Rio. The boys are fitted for tuxes and the girls paint their faces (literally). When the big night arrives, surprises abound for everyone... and in true Acme Loo fashion, unadulterated chaos reigns.

title: Hare Today, Gone Tomorrow
description: Buster is taken captive by crazed animal lover Elmyra (her big debut), and finds she's been holding other Tiny Toons hostage for "years". With Babs' help, Buster and the other toons manage to escape Elmyra's house and deal with her in true cartoon style.

title: Cinemaniacs!
description: Buster and Babs browse the huge selection of films at their local theatre, including "Superbabs," "Duck Trek" and "Pasadena Jones."

title: You Asked for It: Part 1
description: Plucky tries to fix the rigged "request day" machine. Includes "Debutante Devil," "Slight Of Hare," and "Duck Out Of Luck." Part 1 of 2

title: Gang Busters
description: Montana Max and his gang steal a slushie machine and frame Buster for it; Plucky acts as his lawyer and they both get thrown in jail, then try to break out and make Max confess, but encounter one ridiculous obstacle after another in the big house.

title: Citizen Max
description: The isolated and rich Montana Max one day opens his mansions' window, shouting out the word 'Acme.' Hampton goes on a quest to then find out what this strange utterance could mean. His journey takes him on a quest through Max's poor past, and into his huge (but scandalous) run for Class President.

title: Wake Up Call of the Wild
description: The Bunnys consider instinct and their relation to the wild creatures. Includes "Migrant Mallard," "It's A Jungle Out There, and "Kitty Cat-Astrophe."

title: Buster and the Wolverine
description: Re-working of Peter and the Wolf with Tiny Toons cast.

title: You Asked for It: Part 2
description: Dizzy and Hamton are "The Weird Couple," Plucky takes on Monty's polluting factory in"The Return Of The Toxic Revenger" and Hamton clings to his diet in "Little Cake Of Horrors." Part 2 of 2

title: Hollywood Plucky
description: Buster and Babs are in a race with Plucky to see who can get to Hollywood and sell their story to famed director Cooper Daville first. Plucky and Hamton are the first ones to reach Hollywood but have to endure many wild and zany antics to try and reach Mr. Daville.

title: Europe in 30 Minutes
description: Plucky, Hamton and the Bunnys go abroad for a tour of Europe.

title: The Wacko World of Sports
description: Bjorn Bunny thwarts Max's rigged tennis tournament in "Tennis The Menace." Dizzy and Furrball try to fool Arnold in "Bleacher Bummer," and the Vanderbunnys teach Roderick and Rhubella a lesson in "Miniature Golf."

title: Rainy Daze
description: Buster and Babs present three cartoons on how to cope with a rainy day. Rent-A-Friend: Buster's working as a rent-a-friend and gets stuck having to play with Montana Max. Bunny Daze: Babs has the house to herself while her mother's away and daydreams herself into adventures as she does her chores. Fur-Gone Conclusion: Buster and Babs get sick of the rain and head for Aruba but make a wrong turn and wind up at the North Pole, and help save a baby seal from Gotcha Grabmor, a fur scalper.

title: Fields of Honey
description: When Babs bemoans her lack of a female mentor, a mysterious voice leads her to rediscover the forgotten Warner Bros. star, Honey.

title: Sawdust and Toonsil
description: The toons try to free Wackyland creatures trapped in a circus sideshow.

title: Spring in Acme Acres
description: Concord takes over Cupid's job in "Love Among The Toons." Elmyra goes wild while cleaning house in "Elmyra's Spring Cleaning" and Plucky and Dizzy battle for prizes on a humiliating game show in "That's Incredibly Stupid."

title: Psychic Fun-omenon Day
description: Calamaty Coyote sees his life flash before his eyes in "Piece Of Mind." Hamton wimps out of dissecting a frog in class in "Class Cut-Up." A bored Plucky uses binoculars to snoop from his hospital bed in "Rear Window Pain."

title: The Wide World of Elmyra
description: Tyrone Turtle must cross a highway to escape Elmyra in "Turtle Hurdle." Elmyra bungles her babysitting in "Drooley Davey" and friendly dog Barky Marky loses his love of fetch after playing with Elmyra in "Go Fetch."

title: A Ditch in Time
description: Plucky builds a time machine to avoid failing a class.

title: Career Oppor-Toon-ities
description: The toons get part-time jobs. As fast-food workers the Bunnys must serve Max in "Buster's Guide To Part Time Jobs." Toy salesman Hamton assists Elmyra in "Working Pig."

title: Strange Tales of Weird Science
description: A scientist spills a hunger-inducing flavor-enhancer on Hamton in "Scentimental Pig." Sweetie programs Furrball to want to eat "Pit Bullied." Plucky the Toxic Revenger attacks Max's polluting ice-cream-spoon factory in "Duck In The Muck."

title: Inside Plucky Duck
description: The Bunnys travel through Plucky's brain and encounter a costumed Plucky relating the story of his superhero adventures in "Bat's All Folks." Plucky gets stuck in the all-eyeball state on class picture day in "Wild Takes Class."

title: The Acme Bowl
description: Acme Loo's winless season is no deterence to Perfecto kids determined to ensure their team will win the game.

title: Dating, Acme Acres Style
description: Buster and Babs create the rules as they go on a date in "Buster's Guide To Dating." Fifi thinks a tarred and feathered Calamity is another skunk in "Love Stinks." And Elmyra looks for love on "The Dating Game."

title: Looniversity Daze
description: Buster's friends worry about his safety when he's sent to the principal's office in "The Learning Principal," Sweetie searches for Bookworm in "Eating Between The Lines" and Plucky runs into Elmyra when he fakes illness in "What's Up Nurse."

title: Best o' Plucky Duck Day
description: Plucky panics as Granny begins quizzing the class and handing out grueling homework punishments for wrong answers in "One Minute Till Three." Plucky swipes a candy bar in "Sticky Feathers Duck,".

title: Hero Hamton
description: Hamton faces off against Montana Max.

title: Whale's Tales
description: The toons set out to restore a kidnapped bbay whale and punish its abducter.

title: Ask Mr. Popular
description: Dizzy's transformed into the perfect friend when Mr. Popular hooks him up to a personality implanter in "Dapper Diz." Hamton's imaginary friends turns into a jerk in "A Pigment Of His Imagination."

title: Son of Looniversity Daze
description: Plucky's guilt drives him insane in "Plucky's Dastardly Deed," Hamton is frustrated by his hyper-intelligent locker in "Open And Shut Case" and Plucky, Buster and Hamton try to move a piano down from the top of a tower in "C Flat Or B Sharp?"

title: Mr. Popular's Rules of Cool!
description: Hamton tries to get into a cool dance club in "Mr. Popular's Rules Of Cool," Plucky and Hamton compete in a parody of "Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles" in "Slugfest" and Max hunts a street-smart deer in "Venison Anyone?"

title: Fairy Tales for the 90's
description: Buster is mistaken for a brought-to-life toy in "Bunnochio," and Elmyra plays Goldilocks in "Bear Necessities."

title: Who Bopped Bugs Bunny?
description: Daffy is framed for the kidnapping of Bugs Bunny, and the tiny toons try to break him out of jail while solving the crime.

title: Tiny Toon Music Television
description: Max sings motown, Buster spoofs the Sorcerer's Apprentice and Babs performs "Respect" in this parody of MTV.

title: The Return of the Acme Acres Zone
description: "Bladehunter"-parodying Buster hunts for missing robots in "Real Kids Don't Like Broccoli." Hamton and Plucky visit a haunted castle in seach of a phone in "Boo Hoo Hoo" and Duck Dodger and sidekick Plucky battle Marvin the Martian and sidekick Marcia in "Duck Dodgers Jr."

title: The Acme Home Shopping Show
description: Plucky uses an unusual feature of his remote control to "pause" reality in "Oh For Art's Sake." Elmyra torments three bears with her singing in "Teddy Bears Picnic." Babs babysits a devilish charge in "I Was A Teenage Bunnysitter."

title: Weirdest Story Ever Told
description: Buster plays the virtuous highwayman in "Robin Hare," Babs tries to prove her talent to Shakespeare in "To Babs Or Not To Babs," and Buster suffers a nightmare in "Elmyra's Round The World."

title: Viewer Mail Day
description: Hamton and Plucky spend a night in a haunted Irish castle in "Pluck Of The Irish," Elmyra chases Fifi in "Out Of Odor" and Plucky tries to sway a greedy couple who want to eat roast duck in "Buttering Up The Butterfields."

title: Son of the Wacko World of Sports
description: Bjorn Bunny thwarts Max's rigged tennis tournament in "Tennis The Menace." Dizzy and Furrball try to fool Arnold in "Bleacher Bummer," and the Vanderbunnys teach Roderick and Rhubella a lesson in "Miniature Golf."

title: Pollution Solution
description: Superhero Plucky teaches Elmyra how to recycle in "No Deposit, No Return Of The Trash Bag Dispenser." The Bunnys battle the greenhouse effect in "Jungle Bunny" and Max dumps factory waste in Wackyland in "Waste Deep In Wackyland."

title: You Asked for It Again
description: Buster displays classic procrastination techniques instead of doing homework in "Buster's Guide To Goofing Off." Elmyra terrorizes a mall afterhours in "Elmyra At The Mall." In "Hold The Sugar," the world's only sugar-hating ant tells his story.

title: Brave Tales of Real Rabbits
description: Max and the Bunnies do a version of Sherlock Holmes and Dr. Moriarity in "And All That Rot." Buster-as-knight must rescue damsel-in-distress Babs in "Day For Knight."

title: How Sweetie It Is
description: An eagle thinks he's Sweetie's father in "Egged-On Eagle." Sweetie is insulted when Furrball declines to eat her in "Let's Do Lunch." Sweetie performs as Poe's famous bird in "The Raven."

title: New Character Day
description: A host of new characters are auditioned, including "The Roches," singing roach sisters who play in Hamton's kitchen. Plucky dreams he's a private eye in "The Return Of Pluck Twacy."

title: Here's Hamton
description: Plucky and Buster try to make Hamton laugh so hard he'll snort milk out his nose in "Milk, It Makes A Body Spurt." A television program convinces Plucky that Hamton's a wanted criminal in "America's Least Wanted."

title: No Toon Is an Island
description: Hamton, Plucky and the Bunnys search for treasure despite warnings of a certain green-eyed monster.

title: K-ACME TV
description: The Bunnies take over the television station.

title: High Toon
description: The Bunnies become lost in a ghost town being terrorized by coyote bandits.

title: Buster and Babs Go Hawaiian
description: Fed up with mediocre scripts, Buster and Babs burrow their way to Amblin Entertainment, and have a heart-to-heart with Steven Spielberg. Feeling for their plight, Steven gives the two a script written by three 8th graders, called 'Buster and Babs go Hawaiian.' The two take to the project immediately-that is, until Buster realizes part of the script takes place on an airplane (his contract stipulates he won't do plane scenes). Needless to say, Buster's pleas to the writers go unheeded, and the show goes on.

title: Kon Ducki
description: 'Kon Ducki' is Plucky Duck's adaptation of a literary work, telling how one duck dared to prove to the Explorer's Club that ducks did not fly to Salinas to migrate, but actually sailed by boat. With the bet that he can reach Salinas in 21 days, Captain Pluck and his intrepid crew set out to prove his theory. Also included is a 'making of' special, wherein Plucky recounts the journey to bring his vision to the screen.

title: Thirteensomething
description: On a dare from Buster, Babs travels to New York City to try and land a role on the new hit teen drama "thirteensomething". However, Babs finds that fame and fortune isn't all it's cracked up to be.

title: Two-Tone Town
description: Buster and Babs, after hearing that Warner Bros. is replacing Tiny Toons with a new show, try to help three down-on-their-luck characters from the studio's black-and-white past get hired for it.

title: Buster's Directorial Debut
description: Buster sits behind the camera for the first time, but his directorial debut is interrupted by Babs' fitness plan (and a trip to Sandy Witch's house), as well as Plucky's ego (which Buster deals with in a smashing way).

title: Music Day
description: It's Music Day on the show, with three shorts related to the subject. In "Ruffled Ruffie", rock-and-roll fan Buster does battle with a sappy Raffi clone. "The Horn Blows at Lunchtime" features Little Sneezer, a trumpet, a block of stinky cheese and a lot of finger-pointing. "Loon Lake" has Shirley dealing with a group of snooty swan ballerinas, with Babs' help.

title: The Horror of Slumber Party Mountain
It's a Wonderful Tiny Toons Christmas Special
description: Buster Bunny is trying to produce and direct the Tiny Toons Holiday Special, but it is not working. Montana max, makes him look bad, and then bribes the network executives into firing Buster and making him the producer. Buster thinks he has had it, and plans to throw himself out of cartoons forever. His guardian angel appears and shows him what Tiny Toons would be like without him.
